532
00:35:09,609 --> 00:35:12,738
If we can just get past this for Kang Baek's sake...

533
00:35:12,738 --> 00:35:15,609
- If we can do that— 
 - Is he your only grandson?

534
00:35:15,609 --> 00:35:17,008
Then what about my children?

535
00:35:17,008 --> 00:35:19,919
Why do you have to arrest the father of my children for Kang Baek?

536
00:35:19,919 --> 00:35:22,739
Why? Why should I let you do that?

537
00:35:23,749 --> 00:35:27,758
Do you think I can even breathe in that house?

538
00:35:27,758 --> 00:35:29,629
Did you even think about it?

539
00:35:29,629 --> 00:35:32,488
Did you even think how it must have been for me?

540
00:35:32,488 --> 00:35:34,372
Please.

541
00:35:37,169 --> 00:35:41,009
I'm done acting as your insurance policy now.

542
00:36:00,019 --> 00:36:01,802
Moo Ryul.

543
00:36:01,802 --> 00:36:04,126
What's this?

544
00:36:04,126 --> 00:36:06,260
Where did you get this?

545
00:36:06,260 --> 00:36:08,658
You'd better not do what you're about to do.

546
00:36:08,658 --> 00:36:12,702
Or I'll have to come up with more scandalous news!

547
00:36:12,702 --> 00:36:14,987
Was it you?

548
00:36:17,309 --> 00:36:19,408
Did you send these pictures to me?

549
00:36:19,408 --> 00:36:20,538
What do you mean?

550
00:36:20,538 --> 00:36:23,547
You sent the same pictures to me.

551
00:36:24,649 --> 00:36:27,352
You should have done this from the get-go.

552
00:36:27,352 --> 00:36:28,978
It looks like this was bound to happen all along.

553
00:36:28,978 --> 00:36:31,549
What are you talking about? I never sent you any pictures.

554
00:36:31,549 --> 00:36:34,556
Why would I send you these pictures?

555
00:36:36,488 --> 00:36:39,288
Since the whole country would end up seeing the pictures,

556
00:36:39,288 --> 00:36:41,598
I guess it wouldn't have hurt to send them to me first.

557
00:36:41,598 --> 00:36:43,968
Kang Baek! That's enough!

558
00:36:43,968 --> 00:36:45,924
I won't do it.

559
00:36:47,638 --> 00:36:49,310
What?

560
00:36:49,310 --> 00:36:54,091
I won't do what you're worried about.

561
00:36:54,091 --> 00:36:57,108
I don't have time to waste here, so get out of my way.

562
00:36:57,108 --> 00:36:58,829
Are you sure?

563
00:36:58,829 --> 00:37:01,218
How? What else can you do?

564
00:37:01,218 --> 00:37:03,079
Move!

565
00:37:03,079 --> 00:37:06,389
I'm on my way to fix this, so all of us can get out of this.

566
00:37:30,878 --> 00:37:32,982
Honey.

567
00:37:32,982 --> 00:37:35,909
Why didn't you sleep some more?

568
00:37:35,909 --> 00:37:39,468
How could I? After what happened last night.

569
00:37:39,468 --> 00:37:42,844
You were turning and tossing all night.

570
00:37:47,028 --> 00:37:50,368
There really is no news article about Professor Na.

571
00:37:50,368 --> 00:37:52,788
You're really amazing.

572
00:37:52,788 --> 00:37:55,339
You just made a few late-night phone calls.

573
00:37:55,339 --> 00:37:58,635
It's a temporary fix.

574
00:37:58,635 --> 00:38:02,779
If I don't fix it properly, it will leak soon.

575
00:38:03,608 --> 00:38:07,516
By the way, what is Hye Ryul planning to do?

576
00:38:11,649 --> 00:38:16,658
Goodness. You never discuss important matters with me.

577
00:38:16,658 --> 00:38:20,275
At times, the less you know, the better it is.

578
00:38:21,758 --> 00:38:25,167
Right. That's true.

579
00:38:44,448 --> 00:38:46,517
Butler Yang.

580
00:38:48,718 --> 00:38:50,366
Yes, ma'am.

581
00:38:51,089 --> 00:38:54,500
- And the news articles? 
 - None, ma'am.

582
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:58,423
I searched online as well. There's none.

583
00:38:58,423 --> 00:39:02,249
It seems it's all right so far.

584
00:39:02,249 --> 00:39:04,075
Okay.

585
00:39:05,309 --> 00:39:10,513
I would like to pray with you today.

586
00:39:12,749 --> 00:39:16,064
- Really? 
 - Yes.

587
00:39:16,064 --> 00:39:18,590
For Kang Baek.

588
00:39:30,169 --> 00:39:32,341
Thank you.

589
00:39:35,298 --> 00:39:38,431
It's been a long time since I prayed.

590
00:39:39,638 --> 00:39:42,482
He may answer my prayer.

591
00:39:43,548 --> 00:39:46,085
Has it been 40 years?

592
00:39:48,348 --> 00:39:50,876
It's already been that long.

593
00:39:51,849 --> 00:39:56,960
I wondered if He had abandoned me.

594
00:39:58,558 --> 00:40:02,823
In the end, I resented Him a lot.

595
00:40:02,823 --> 00:40:05,110
That can't be true.

596
00:40:05,798 --> 00:40:09,343
He wouldn't abandon His children.

597
00:40:10,139 --> 00:40:12,074
Besides,

598
00:40:12,074 --> 00:40:16,729
I've always been praying

599
00:40:16,729 --> 00:40:19,521
for you

600
00:40:19,521 --> 00:40:21,484
and...

601
00:40:21,484 --> 00:40:25,397
your late son as well.

602
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:28,395
Yes.

603
00:40:29,558 --> 00:40:31,954
I know.

604
00:40:34,899 --> 00:40:40,191
That's why I was always grateful.

605
00:40:51,149 --> 00:40:53,388
Father.

606
00:40:54,079 --> 00:40:57,150
Please protect Kang Baek.

607
00:40:57,988 --> 00:41:04,649
Please listen to my prayer and show Kang Baek a path to take.

608
00:41:04,649 --> 00:41:07,596
Please save Kang Baek,

609
00:41:08,599 --> 00:41:14,099
Ms. Han, and Ms. Ham.

610
00:41:14,099 --> 00:41:16,348
If you answer my prayer,

611
00:41:16,348 --> 00:41:18,168
I will

612
00:41:19,508 --> 00:41:23,925
believe with all of my heart

613
00:41:23,925 --> 00:41:27,801
that you're generous and benevolent.

614
00:41:28,548 --> 00:41:30,385
Lord.

615
00:41:35,919 --> 00:41:38,587
No. I'm on my way to work.

616
00:41:38,587 --> 00:41:42,164
You're a lawyer, so you can go see him.

617
00:41:42,164 --> 00:41:43,829
Take me with you.

618
00:41:43,829 --> 00:41:47,133
That's only the case if I represent your father,

619
00:41:47,133 --> 00:41:50,969
but your father said he didn't want a lawyer.

620
00:41:50,969 --> 00:41:52,569
Then what do we do?

621
00:41:52,569 --> 00:41:54,738
Someone should go there and help him.

622
00:41:54,738 --> 00:41:59,008
My dad... Are we going to leave him alone in there?

623
00:41:59,008 --> 00:42:00,419
As if we're abandoning him?

624
00:42:00,419 --> 00:42:03,550
Enough! Like I said, there's nothing I can do!

625
00:42:05,289 --> 00:42:09,519
Grandpa!

626
00:42:09,519 --> 00:42:11,667
Grandpa!

627
00:42:23,638 --> 00:42:27,175
All right. Let's do it.

628
00:42:28,079 --> 00:42:30,379
I wish we could've done this sooner.

629
00:42:30,379 --> 00:42:35,519
That family sure likes to complicate things.

630
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:39,849
So the real culprit that crazy Dolphin knows...

631
00:42:39,849 --> 00:42:42,353
Why did he kill Hong Nan Hee?

632
00:42:43,829 --> 00:42:47,813
He just hit her on the spur of the moment.

633
00:42:47,813 --> 00:42:50,568
Maybe he's a junkie and was caught using drugs.

634
00:42:50,568 --> 00:42:52,928
Oh, I see. So that's it.

635
00:42:52,928 --> 00:42:55,838
A junkie's spur-of-the-moment murder while high on drugs.

636
00:42:55,838 --> 00:42:58,108
That's how you'll wrap it up?

637
00:42:58,108 --> 00:43:02,178
Oh my, people will be so bored now with nothing to chew out.

638
00:43:02,178 --> 00:43:06,249
They'll no longer see Jusung on the news.

639
00:43:06,249 --> 00:43:08,084
Right, Mr. Ko?

640
00:43:09,749 --> 00:43:13,408
Yes, I'll make sure it won't happen.

641
00:43:13,408 --> 00:43:16,858
Don't forget that you're making this promise with your life on the line.

642
00:43:16,858 --> 00:43:19,329
From now on, let's get along.

643
00:43:19,329 --> 00:43:22,085
Okay, Ko Won Kyung?

644
00:43:22,085 --> 00:43:25,199
- Yes, sir. 
 - Come on. Think of me as a brother.

645
00:43:25,199 --> 00:43:28,000
Call me by my first name like before. Drop the honorifics.

646
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:31,838
That day, I said that out of anger,

647
00:43:31,838 --> 00:43:36,238
but hearing you talking so politely makes me uncomfortable.

648
00:43:38,408 --> 00:43:40,778
Let's just go back to the old-time way.

649
00:43:40,778 --> 00:43:43,023
- Yes, sir. 
 - Hey, come on.

650
00:43:44,019 --> 00:43:47,706
- Okay, Jang Il.
 - Good.

651
00:43:49,758 --> 00:43:51,698
So this is all you need?

652
00:43:56,099 --> 00:43:57,482
Open it.

653
00:44:10,048 --> 00:44:11,949
   

654
00:44:11,949 --> 00:44:13,689
   

655
00:44:17,249 --> 00:44:21,680
It'll be taken care of today as you promised, right?

656
00:44:21,680 --> 00:44:24,528
Goodness. Don't you worry.

657
00:44:24,528 --> 00:44:27,729
Just one phone call and they'll head over to the police station.

658
00:44:27,729 --> 00:44:30,629
Oh, it's lunchtime already.

659
00:44:30,629 --> 00:44:32,169
What should we order?

660
00:44:32,169 --> 00:44:36,138
Ms. Jung! Call Golden Castle!

661
00:44:36,138 --> 00:44:40,738
Hey, why the long face? Smile a little, will you?

662
00:44:40,738 --> 00:44:43,548
You're a prosecutor, yet you can't keep a poker face?

663
00:44:43,548 --> 00:44:47,545
You have a big face, so it shows easily.

664
00:44:47,545 --> 00:44:50,988
Once he's behind bars, he won't get out until the day he dies anyway.

665
00:44:50,988 --> 00:44:53,818
He's a total scumbag.

666
00:44:53,818 --> 00:44:57,928
He sold drugs to kids.

667
00:44:57,928 --> 00:45:01,559
Thanks to this, he'll go to jail for murder.

668
00:45:01,559 --> 00:45:03,628
It'll make things a little easier for his family,

669
00:45:03,628 --> 00:45:06,229
and our society will become a bit cleaner.

670
00:45:06,229 --> 00:45:08,892
It's a win-win for everyone.

671
00:45:10,068 --> 00:45:13,809
Other people think that we caught the real culprit.

672
00:45:13,809 --> 00:45:16,213
Yes, I know that.

673
00:45:18,179 --> 00:45:19,614
Hold on, but...

674
00:45:20,818 --> 00:45:23,818
Did Han Hye Ryul buy that?

675
00:45:23,818 --> 00:45:26,479
She has nothing to do with this.

676
00:45:26,479 --> 00:45:29,658
What are you talking about? Do you think I'm an idiot?

677
00:45:29,658 --> 00:45:33,028
You don't have a single card to present to Chief Jang.

678
00:45:33,028 --> 00:45:36,599
Of course, Han Hye Ryul will take the lead and try to strike a deal.

679
00:45:36,599 --> 00:45:40,838
All right. That's not important now.

680
00:45:40,838 --> 00:45:44,709
We should move quickly so that Professor Na can have dinner at home later today,

681
00:45:44,709 --> 00:45:48,108
and that way, you can be released soon too.

682
00:45:48,108 --> 00:45:51,249
Okay, let's drop this. I'm tired.

683
00:45:52,948 --> 00:45:59,019
You know, since I'm already here, I want to stay for dinner.

684
00:45:59,019 --> 00:46:01,223
Is that okay, Mr. Ko?

685
00:46:02,818 --> 00:46:05,302
Sure, suit yourself.

686
00:46:06,899 --> 00:46:09,358
What shall I do until my food arrives?

687
00:46:09,358 --> 00:46:11,478
Do you know how to play Go?

688
00:46:14,139 --> 00:46:16,174
After that,

689
00:46:16,174 --> 00:46:20,538
I saw the iron pipe lying around, so I grabbed it without thinking...

690
00:46:20,538 --> 00:46:23,518
I swear, I didn't know she'd die like that.

691
00:46:24,949 --> 00:46:27,805
Then I threw the body

692
00:46:27,805 --> 00:46:29,884
into the lake.

693
00:46:30,789 --> 00:46:33,430
You know, like those scenes you see in dramas...

694
00:46:33,430 --> 00:46:35,465
Okay, then...

695
00:46:35,465 --> 00:46:38,550
Where is the murder weapon? The iron pipe.

696
00:46:41,258 --> 00:46:45,447
You keep insisting that you're the culprit,

697
00:46:45,447 --> 00:46:47,599
so you must know.

698
00:46:47,599 --> 00:46:50,686
Oh, that's...

699
00:46:51,769 --> 00:46:54,132
Well, what did I do with it?

700
00:46:55,338 --> 00:46:58,631
Right. I threw it in the lake too.

701
00:47:03,378 --> 00:47:04,691
Here.

702
00:47:22,599 --> 00:47:24,179
Excuse us for a moment.

703
00:47:29,338 --> 00:47:31,871
Hey, isn't it that bag?

704
00:47:36,119 --> 00:47:39,758
Yes, the purse she was wearing.

705
00:47:39,758 --> 00:47:42,693
It wasn't found at the scene.

706
00:48:01,179 --> 00:48:03,139
   

707
00:48:03,139 --> 00:48:04,826
Shoot.

708
00:48:10,449 --> 00:48:12,208
   

709
00:48:14,059 --> 00:48:17,718
 Hey, Yoon Eun Mi! What is your problem? 

710
00:48:17,718 --> 00:48:18,988
Have you lost your mind?

711
00:48:18,988 --> 00:48:22,081
You're there, yet you didn't report this to me?

712
00:48:22,081 --> 00:48:24,429
Nothing is for certain yet.

713
00:48:24,429 --> 00:48:27,398
The investigators haven't confirmed it yet.

714
00:48:27,398 --> 00:48:29,669
Besides, it's just so strange.

715
00:48:29,669 --> 00:48:32,008
He was never even considered a suspect.

716
00:48:32,008 --> 00:48:35,539
He has no ties to her. How am I supposed to believe he killed her?

717
00:48:35,539 --> 00:48:39,568
On top of that, he turned himself in?  Isn't something fishy here?

718
00:48:39,568 --> 00:48:42,218
We should speak with the investigators in charge and—

719
00:48:42,218 --> 00:48:46,048
And we'll lose the scoop while you do that?

720
00:48:46,048 --> 00:48:49,788
 It hasn't been made official yet, but the Chief Superintendent has already admitted it. 

721
00:48:49,788 --> 00:48:53,798
A press briefing has been scheduled. Everyone's on their way there now.

722
00:48:53,798 --> 00:48:56,729
Isn't that enough to make it a fact, which you love?

723
00:48:56,729 --> 00:48:58,798
 He's a drug addict. 

724
00:48:58,798 --> 00:49:01,738
 Have you never seen an insane man beat up a woman to death? 

725
00:49:01,738 --> 00:49:06,309
Everyone in the country was looking for the killer, so I bet he got scared and turned himself in.

726
00:49:06,309 --> 00:49:08,108
Just say, "The real culprit has turned himself in."

727
00:49:08,108 --> 00:49:10,139
"She died after an altercation with a drug addict."

728
00:49:10,139 --> 00:49:12,879
Just do that in front of the police station.

729
00:49:12,879 --> 00:49:16,519
-   That picture is all we need.  
 - Even so...

730
00:49:16,519 --> 00:49:20,775
Say, "Whether or not sexual assault was his goal is unknown."

731
00:49:23,119 --> 00:49:25,428
I can't do that, sir.

732
00:49:25,428 --> 00:49:28,858
- I'm sorry. 
 -  What? Hey! 

733
00:49:28,858 --> 00:49:31,043
Hey, I'm sorry.

734
00:49:31,043 --> 00:49:33,117
I can't do this.

735
00:49:33,128 --> 00:49:35,139
You guys should head back to the office first.

736
00:49:35,139 --> 00:49:38,419
I need to speak with the detectives in charge of the case.

737
00:49:39,168 --> 00:49:41,692
- Okay, it's fine. 
 - Sorry.

738
00:49:51,548 --> 00:49:52,789
 This just came in. 

739
00:49:52,789 --> 00:49:57,289
 The investigation on the law school student murder has taken a new turn. 

740
00:49:57,289 --> 00:50:01,499
 Earlier today, the real culprit turned himself in. 

741
00:50:01,499 --> 00:50:03,329
 Park, the accused, was drunk at the time. 

742
00:50:03,329 --> 00:50:06,568
 He ran into Hong, the victim, while roaming the campus. 

743
00:50:06,568 --> 00:50:10,938
 He insists that they got into an argument because she made condescending remarks without an apology. 

744
00:50:10,938 --> 00:50:16,008
 He confessed that he killed Hong and threw the body into the lake 

745
00:50:16,008 --> 00:50:17,649
 in order to destroy evidence. 

746
00:50:17,649 --> 00:50:20,878
 Park is a former drug convict with multiple priors. 

747
00:50:20,878 --> 00:50:24,379
 He seemed to be under the influence of drugs even when he turned himself in. 

748
00:50:24,379 --> 00:50:29,119
Park's statement and the evidence submitted by him

749
00:50:29,119 --> 00:50:33,028
give us enough reason to believe that he is telling the truth.

750
00:50:33,028 --> 00:50:38,549
So at the moment, we believe that Park is the real culprit.

751
00:50:38,549 --> 00:50:44,469
We, the police, sincerely apologize for causing you concern.

752
00:50:44,469 --> 00:50:47,669
- Are you taking questions? 
 - Can we get a comment?

753
00:50:50,608 --> 00:50:53,108
Was this it? This was it, after all?

754
00:50:53,108 --> 00:50:55,449
You said we'd all be able to breathe at last.

755
00:50:55,449 --> 00:50:58,548
Are we using another innocent person?

756
00:50:58,548 --> 00:51:01,152
What are you talking about?

757
00:51:01,152 --> 00:51:03,218
It's not what you think, Kang Baek!

758
00:51:03,218 --> 00:51:05,688
That man killed Hong Nan Hee.

759
00:51:05,688 --> 00:51:07,129
We received a tip-off.

760
00:51:07,129 --> 00:51:09,999
Liar. You're lying!

761
00:51:09,999 --> 00:51:14,323
Mom, you know it's not true. You don't believe it either!

762
00:51:15,269 --> 00:51:16,669
Kang Baek.

763
00:51:16,669 --> 00:51:18,676
Let's stop now.

764
00:51:18,676 --> 00:51:22,079
Doing all these horrible things... Let's stop, please!

765
00:51:22,079 --> 00:51:24,535
Let's please stop, Mom!

766
00:51:25,209 --> 00:51:27,449
Please.

767
00:51:27,449 --> 00:51:28,933
Please...

768
00:51:30,048 --> 00:51:32,669
Please stop, Mom.

769
00:51:32,669 --> 00:51:34,296
Kang Baek.

770
00:51:36,559 --> 00:51:38,388
Kang Baek.

771
00:51:38,388 --> 00:51:39,329
Kang Baek.

772
00:51:39,329 --> 00:51:43,309
Mom, please stop...

773
00:51:45,529 --> 00:51:47,177
Mom, stop...

774
00:51:48,539 --> 00:51:50,439
Stop...

775
00:51:53,569 --> 00:51:55,053
It's okay.

776
00:52:03,579 --> 00:52:05,407
 Because I... 

777
00:52:07,519 --> 00:52:09,367
 I'm gay. 

778
00:52:10,388 --> 00:52:13,729
 Doing all these horrible things... Let's stop, please. 

779
00:52:13,729 --> 00:52:16,198
 Please stop, Mom! 

780
00:52:16,198 --> 00:52:17,883
 Stop... 

